  "notes": [
    "Pinned OCI SDK contract: the provider resource exposes CreateBdsInstance, GetBdsInstance, ListBdsInstances, UpdateBdsInstance, and DeleteBdsInstance plus auxiliary Add*, Change*, ExecuteBootstrapScript, and RemoveKafka mutations; the paired datasource oci_bds_bds_instances filters compartment_id, display_name, and state and returns bds_instances from the SDK Items list.",
    "Pinned provider implementation: create and update paths use WaitForUpdatedState and expose a broader mutable surface than the published runtime, including compartment moves, node-shape growth, network updates, state transitions, and trigger-style helper actions. The reviewed generatedruntime client does not run those provider-owned waiters or auxiliary mutators; it follows plain write calls with read-after-write or confirm-delete rereads instead.",
    "Repo-authored lifecycle classification stays explicit: runtime treats CREATING as provisioning, UPDATING/SUSPENDING/RESUMING as updating, ACTIVE/INACTIVE/SUSPENDED as success, FAILED as terminal without requeue, and delete confirmation follows DELETING to DELETED or NotFound.",
    "Repo-authored bind-versus-create and mutation policy stay explicit: pre-create lookup matches exact compartmentId plus displayName; only displayName, bootstrapScriptUrl, freeformTags, definedTags, and kmsKeyId reconcile in place. CompartmentId, clusterVersion, isHighAvailability, isSecure, clusterProfile, networkConfig, and nodes remain replacement-only drift, while clusterAdminPassword, clusterPublicKey, and kerberosRealmName stay create-time inputs."
  ]
